  <Docs>
    <summary>Provides options for controlling the output of an XPS document.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKDocumentXpsOptions` is a value type that controls how Skia renders pages
when writing an XPS document. Pass it to one of the
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKDocument.CreateXps*> overloads.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var options = new SKDocumentXpsOptions { Dpi = 150 };
using var stream = new SKFileWStream("output.xps");
using var doc = SKDocument.CreateXps(stream, options);
using var canvas = doc.BeginPage(595, 842);
canvas.DrawColor(SKColors.White);
doc.EndPage();
doc.Close();
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
